name: Annual report
text: The director of commerce and consumer affairs shall prepare and submit to the legislature annually, twenty days prior to the convening of each regular session, a report containing the director's evaluation of the operation and effects of this chapter.  The report shall include a summary of the claims brought before the design professional conciliation panel and the disposition of those claims. [L 1981, c 228, pt of §1; am L 1982, c 204, §8; am L 1983, c 124, §17; gen ch 1985]
